{{!--
  Screenshot Table Partial
  Displays screenshots in a two-column HTML table for the README.

  Expected context:
    - screenshots        {array}   Screenshot objects from screenshots.json.
                                   Each has: id, file, alt, category, notes?, status
    - screenshotCategory {string}  Filter value for the `category` field.
                                   Defaults to "readme" when omitted.
                                   Pass an empty string "" to include all screenshots.

  Handlebars helpers required by the build script:
    - eq(a, b)           → strict equality test (returns boolean)
    - isOdd(n)           → returns true when n is odd (used to close/open <tr> pairs)

  Only screenshots whose `status` is "captured" are rendered; pending and
  outdated entries are silently skipped so placeholders do not appear in the
  published README.

  To render a simple flat list instead of the table (better for some mobile
  renderers), replace the HTML table block below with the commented-out
  Markdown list alternative at the bottom of this file.
--}}
## Screenshots

<table>
<tr>
{{#each screenshots}}
{{#if (eq category (or ../screenshotCategory "readme"))}}
{{#if (eq status "captured")}}
<td align="center" width="50%">
<img src="{{file}}" alt="{{alt}}" width="100%">
<br>
<em>{{#if notes}}{{notes}}{{else}}{{alt}}{{/if}}</em>
</td>
{{#if (isOdd @index)}}
</tr>
<tr>
{{/if}}
{{/if}}
{{/if}}
{{/each}}
</tr>
</table>

{{!--
  Alternative: flat Markdown image list (better mobile rendering, no HTML).
  Uncomment and delete the HTML table block above to use this instead.

{{#each screenshots}}
{{#if (eq category (or ../screenshotCategory "readme"))}}
{{#if (eq status "captured")}}
### {{alt}}

![{{alt}}]({{file}})

{{#if notes}}_{{notes}}_{{/if}}

{{/if}}
{{/if}}
{{/each}}
--}}
